FBIS4-17813 "drsov082_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 Georgia New Defense Minister Comments on Appointment New Defense Minister Comments on Appointment LD2604164494 Moscow NTV in Russian 1500 GMT 26 Apr 94 LD2604164494 Moscow NTV Russian BFN [Video report by unidentified correspondent, including recorded comments by Lieutenant General Vardiko Nadibaidze, the new Georgian defense minister] [Excerpts] [Correspondent] At today's Georgian Supreme Council session, deputies were to complete selection of the Cabinet of Ministers. The morning session was entirely taken up with discussions of the appointment of the defense minister. The head of state proposed a serviceman in the Russian Army, Lieutenant General Vardiko Mikhailovich Nadibaidze, deputy commander of the Transcaucasian Group of Russian Forces, for the post. [passage omitted] The new minister hopes to attract his former fellow-servicemen from the Russian Army. [Nadibaidze] Anybody capable of helping and who will help will be next to me. To help set up an army, and to help our people. [Correspondent] On mutual relations with the Russian Armed Forces, the minister said: [Nadibaidze] The majority understand the situation in Georgia, and will help us. I am convinced they will help. And so our relations will be normal.
